  "analytics_identifier": null,
  "base_path": "/expenses-and-benefits-car-parking-charges",
  "content_id": "45e449f8-86f8-4977-bdcb-a0a7c4faf6dc",
  "description": "Tax and reporting rules for employers providing expenses for car parking charges",
  "details": {
    "external_related_links": [

    ],
    "hide_chapter_navigation": false,
    "parts": [
      {
        "body": "<p>As an employer covering the cost of parking charges for your employees, you have certain tax, National Insurance and reporting obligations.</p>\n\n<div role=\"note\" aria-label=\"Information\" class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>There are different rules if you <a href=\"/expenses-and-benefits-parking-spaces\">provide your employee with a parking space</a> directly.</p>\n</div>\n",
        "slug": "overview",
        "title": "Overview"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>You do not have to report anything to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>, or deduct or pay tax and National Insurance, if the charge was for parking at or near your workplace.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"business-journeys\">Business journeys</h2>\n\n<p>You do not need to report anything to <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>, or deduct or pay tax or National Insurance, for parking charges on ‘business journeys’.</p>\n\n<p>A business journey is either:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>made as part of work - like a service engineer travelling to an appointment</li>\n  <li>to a temporary workplace</li>\n</ul>\n\n",
        "slug": "whats-exempt",
        "title": "What's exempt"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>If the parking charge is not <a href=\"/expenses-and-benefits-car-parking-charges/whats-exempt\">exempt</a>, you must report it to <abbr title=\"HM Revenues &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>. You may have to deduct and pay tax and National Insurance on it.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"contracts-with-parking-providers\">Contracts with parking providers</h2>\n\n<p>If you have a contract with a parking provider and you pay them directly, you’ll need to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/employer-reporting-expenses-benefits/reporting-and-paying\">report on form P11D</a></li>\n  <li>pay Class 1A National Insurance on what you pay for the parking</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If your employee has a contract with a parking provider and you pay them directly, you’ll need to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/employer-reporting-expenses-benefits/reporting-and-paying\">report on form P11D</a></li>\n  <li>add what you pay for parking to their other earnings, and deduct and pay Class 1 National Insurance (but not <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"parking-charges-as-earnings\">Parking charges as earnings</h2>\n\n<p>If you give your employee money to pay for parking charges, it counts as earnings and you must:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>add it to your employee’s other earnings</li>\n  <li>deduct and pay <abbr title=\"Pay As You Earn\">PAYE</abbr> tax and Class 1 National Insurance using payroll</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"salary-sacrifice-arrangements\">Salary sacrifice arrangements</h2>\n\n<p>If the cost of the parking charges is less than the amount of salary given up, report the salary amount instead.</p>\n\n<p>These rules do not apply to arrangements made before 6 April 2017 - check <a href=\"/guidance/salary-sacrifice-and-the-effects-on-paye\">when the rules will change</a>.</p>\n\n",
        "slug": "what-to-report-and-pay",
        "title": "What to report and pay"
      },
      {
        "body": "<p>The following guides contain more detailed information:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/eim01030.htm\">car parking facilities at or near the employee’s workplace</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/nimmanual/nim05625.htm\">Class 1 National Insurance - parking fees incurred at the permanent workplace</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/eimanual/eim31820.htm\">travel expenses - incidental costs</a></p>\n  </li>\n  <li>\n    <p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/manuals/nimmanual/nim05620.htm\">Class 1 National Insurance - parking fees incurred in connection with business travel</a></p>\n  </li>\n</ul>\n",
        "slug": "technical-guidance",
        "title": "Technical guidance"
      }
    ]
  },
